{"node_id": "cee4df9f", "title": "Quick decision guide", "path": "choosing-apis > Choosing between Graph and Functional APIs > Quick decision guide", "content": "Use the **Graph API** when you need:\n\n* **Complex workflow visualization** for debugging and documentation\n* **Explicit state management** with shared data across multiple nodes\n* **Conditional branching** with multiple decision points\n* **Parallel execution paths** that need to merge later\n* **Team collaboration** where visual representation aids understanding\n\nUse the **Functional API** when you want:\n\n* **Minimal code changes** to existing procedural code\n* **Standard control flow** (if/else, loops, function calls)\n* **Function-scoped state** without explicit state management\n* **Rapid prototyping** with less boilerplate\n* **Linear workflows** with simple branching logic", "summary": "A guide to help choose between Graph API for complex workflows and state management, and Functional API for minimal code changes and rapid prototyping.", "keywords": ["Graph API", "Functional API", "workflow visualization", "state management", "conditional branching", "parallel execution", "team collaboration", "procedural code", "control flow", "rapid prototyping"]}